{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893226392,"sessionID":"ses_284842a70ffeQCCyWUKDRhFriu","part":{"id":"prt_d7b7c209a001kMyBIt8rsR7Vws","messageID":"msg_d7b7c032d0012W5aPrQq672UfR","sessionID":"ses_284842a70ffeQCCyWUKDRhFriu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-e6b6b1b212f4458699d7c68742422dc6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # delta-spec: AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Module: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n6: Language: Go\n7: Size: L\n8: Task: Add comprehensive unit tests for untested components\n9: \n10: ## Requirements\n11: \n12: ### REQ-001: Unit tests for auth/k8s_auth.go\n13: \n14: **Description:** Implement unit tests for K8sAuthenticator and TokenCache components.\n15: \n16: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n17: \n18: #### SCENARIO-001: K8sAuthenticator authenticates valid token\n19: ```gherkin\n20: GIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface and audience\n21: AND a valid Kubernetes service account token\n22: WHEN Authenticate is called with the token\n23: THEN the AuthenticationInfo should be returned containing username, UID, and groups\n24: AND no error should be returned\n25: ```\n26: \n27: #### SCENARIO-002: K8sAuthenticator rejects invalid token\n28: ```gherkin\n29: GIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface and audience\n30: AND an invalid/expired Kubernetes token\n31: WHEN Authenticate is called with the invalid token\n32: THEN an error should be returned\n33: AND the error message should indicate authentication failed\n34: ```\n35: \n36: #### SCENARIO-003: K8sAuthenticator handles TokenReview API failure\n37: ```gherkin\n38: GIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface\n39: AND the TokenReview API returns an error\n40: WHEN Authenticate is called\n41: THEN an error should be returned\n42: AND the error should wrap the underlying API error\n43: ```\n44: \n45: #### SCENARIO-004: TokenCache stores and retrieves valid entry\n46: ```gherkin\n47: GIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 5 minutes\n48: AND an AuthenticationInfo object\n49: WHEN Put is called with a token and the info\n50: AND Get is called with the same token before TTL expires\n51: THEN the AuthenticationInfo should be returned\n52: AND the second return value should be true\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### SCENARIO-005: TokenCache returns false for non-existent token\n56: ```gherkin\n57: GIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 5 minutes\n58: WHEN Get is called with a token that was never stored\n59: THEN nil should be returned\n60: AND the second return value should be false\n61: ```\n62: \n63: #### SCENARIO-006: TokenCache expires entries after TTL\n64: ```gherkin\n65: GIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 1 millisecond\n66: AND an AuthenticationInfo object stored with Put\n67: WHEN the cache is waited for 2 milliseconds\n68: AND Get is called with the token\n69: THEN nil should be returned\n70: AND the second return value should be false\n71: ```\n72: \n73: #### SCENARIO-007: TokenCache Delete removes entry\n74: ```gherkin\n75: GIVEN a TokenCache with a stored token entry\n76: WHEN Delete is called with the token\n77: AND Get is called with the same token\n78: THEN nil should be returned\n79: AND the second return value should be false\n80: ```\n81: \n82: #### SCENARIO-008: TokenCache Cleanup removes expired entries\n83: ```gherkin\n84: GIVEN a TokenCache with TTL of 1 millisecond\n85: AND multiple token entries stored\n86: WHEN the cache is waited for 2 milliseconds\n87: AND Cleanup is called\n88: THEN expired entries should be removed from the cache\n89: ```\n90: \n91: #### SCENARIO-009: TokenCache is thread-safe for concurrent reads\n92: ```gherkin\n93: GIVEN a TokenCache with multiple stored entries\n94: AND multiple goroutines calling Get concurrently\n95: THEN no race condition should occur\n96: AND all reads should return consistent results\n97: ```\n98: \n99: #### SCENARIO-010: TokenCache is thread-safe for concurrent writes\n100: ```gherkin\n101: GIVEN a TokenCache\n102: AND multiple goroutines calling Put with different tokens concurrently\n103: THEN no race condition should occur\n104: AND all entries should be stored correctly\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### REQ-002: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/predicates.go\n110: \n111: **Description:** Implement unit tests for event predicates and helper functions.\n112: \n113: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n114: \n115: #### SCENARIO-011: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate returns true on generation change\n116: ```gherkin\n117: GIVEN a ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\n118: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld generation = 1\n119: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew generation = 2\n120: WHEN Update is called with the event\n121: THEN true should be returned\n122: ```\n123: \n124: #### SCENARIO-012: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate returns false on same generation\n125: ```gherkin\n126: GIVEN a ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\n127: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld generation = 1\n128: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew generation = 1\n129: WHEN Update is called with the event\n130: THEN false should be returned\n131: ```\n132: \n133: #### SCENARIO-013: ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate returns false on nil objects\n134: ```gherkin\n135: GIVEN a ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate\n136: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld = nil\n137: OR ObjectNew = nil\n138: WHEN Update is called with the event\n139: THEN false should be returned\n140: ```\n141: \n142: #### SCENARIO-014: LabelChangedPredicate returns true when label added\n143: ```gherkin\n144: GIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\n145: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n146: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key\": \"value\", \"newKey\": \"newValue\"}\n147: WHEN Update is called with the event\n148: THEN true should be returned\n149: ```\n150: \n151: #### SCENARIO-015: LabelChangedPredicate returns true when label modified\n152: ```gherkin\n153: GIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\n154: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key\": \"oldValue\"}\n155: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key\": \"newValue\"}\n156: WHEN Update is called with the event\n157: THEN true should be returned\n158: ```\n159: \n160: #### SCENARIO-016: LabelChangedPredicate returns true when label removed\n161: ```gherkin\n162: GIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\n163: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key1\": \"value1\", \"key2\": \"value2\"}\n164: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key1\": \"value1\"}\n165: WHEN Update is called with the event\n166: THEN true should be returned\n167: ```\n168: \n169: #### SCENARIO-017: LabelChangedPredicate returns false on unchanged labels\n170: ```gherkin\n171: GIVEN a LabelChangedPredicate\n172: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n173: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n174: WHEN Update is called with the event\n175: THEN false should be returned\n176: ```\n177: \n178: #### SCENARIO-018: AnnotationChangedPredicate returns true on annotation change\n179: ```gherkin\n180: GIVEN an AnnotationChangedPredicate\n181: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectOld annotations = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n182: AND an UpdateEvent with ObjectNew annotations = {\"key\": \"newValue\"}\n183: WHEN Update is called with the event\n184: THEN true should be returned\n185: ```\n186: \n187: #### SCENARIO-019: PauseAnnotationPredicate returns true when not paused\n188: ```gherkin\n189: GIVEN a PauseAnnotationPredicate\n190: AND a CreateEvent with Object annotations = {}\n191: WHEN Create is called with the event\n192: THEN true should be returned\n193: ```\n194: \n195: #### SCENARIO-020: PauseAnnotationPredicate returns false when paused\n196: ```gherkin\n197: GIVEN a PauseAnnotationPredicate\n198: AND a CreateEvent with Object annotations = {\"agentcube.volcano.sh/paused\": \"true\"}\n199: WHEN Create is called with the event\n200: THEN false should be returned\n201: ```\n202: \n203: #### SCENARIO-021: IsBeingDeleted returns true for object with deletion timestamp\n204: ```gherkin\n205: GIVEN a client.Object with DeletionTimestamp set\n206: WHEN IsBeingDeleted is called with the object\n207: THEN true should be returned\n208: ```\n209: \n210: #### SCENARIO-022: IsBeingDeleted returns false for object without deletion timestamp\n211: ```gherkin\n212: GIVEN a client.Object with zero DeletionTimestamp\n213: WHEN IsBeingDeleted is called with the object\n214: THEN false should be returned\n215: ```\n216: \n217: #### SCENARIO-023: HasOwnerReference returns true when owner reference exists\n218: ```gherkin\n219: GIVEN a client.Object with OwnerReferences containing an owner with UID \"test-uid\"\n220: WHEN HasOwnerReference is called with the object and UID \"test-uid\"\n221: THEN true should be returned\n222: ```\n223: \n224: #### SCENARIO-024: HasOwnerReference returns false when owner reference missing\n225: ```gherkin\n226: GIVEN a client.Object with OwnerReferences not containing UID \"missing-uid\"\n227: WHEN HasOwnerReference is called with the object and UID \"missing-uid\"\n228: THEN false should be returned\n229: ```\n230: \n231: #### SCENARIO-025: AddOwnerReference adds owner reference to object\n232: ```gherkin\n233: GIVEN a child client.Object\n234: AND an owner client.Object\n235: WHEN AddOwnerReference is called with child and owner\n236: THEN the child should have the owner in its OwnerReferences\n237: AND the owner reference should have the correct APIVersion, Kind, UID, and Name\n238: ```\n239: \n240: #### SCENARIO-026: AddLabels adds labels to object\n241: ```gherkin\n242: GIVEN a client.Object with labels = {\"existing\": \"value\"}\n243: WHEN AddLabels is called with labels = {\"new\": \"label\"}\n244: THEN the object should have labels = {\"existing\": \"value\", \"new\": \"label\"}\n245: ```\n246: \n247: #### SCENARIO-027: AddLabels initializes empty labels map\n248: ```gherkin\n249: GIVEN a client.Object with nil labels\n250: WHEN AddLabels is called with labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n251: THEN the object should have labels = {\"key\": \"value\"}\n252: ```\n253: \n254: #### SCENARIO-028: AddAnnotations adds annotations to object\n255: ```gherkin\n256: GIVEN a client.Object with annotations = {\"existing\": \"value\"}\n257: WHEN AddAnnotations is called with annotations = {\"new\": \"annotation\"}\n258: THEN the object should have annotations = {\"existing\": \"value\", \"new\": \"annotation\"}\n259: ```\n260: \n261: #### SCENARIO-029: IsPodReady returns true for ready pod\n262: ```gherkin\n263: GIVEN a Pod with PodReady condition status = ConditionTrue\n264: WHEN IsPodReady is called with the pod\n265: THEN true should be returned\n266: ```\n267: \n268: #### SCENARIO-030: IsPodReady returns false for not ready pod\n269: ```gherkin\n270: GIVEN a Pod with PodReady condition status = ConditionFalse\n271: WHEN IsPodReady is called with the pod\n272: THEN false should be returned\n273: ```\n274: \n275: #### SCENARIO-031: IsPodReady returns false for pod without ready condition\n276: ```gherkin\n277: GIVEN a Pod without PodReady condition\n278: WHEN IsPodReady is called with the pod\n279: THEN false should be returned\n280: ```\n281: \n282: #### SCENARIO-032: GetPodCondition returns matching condition\n283: ```gherkin\n284: GIVEN a Pod with conditions including PodReady\n285: WHEN GetPodCondition is called with PodReady type\n286: THEN the PodReady condition should be returned\n287: ```\n288: \n289: #### SCENARIO-033: GetPodCondition returns nil for missing condition\n290: ```gherkin\n291: GIVEN a Pod without Ready condition\n292: WHEN GetPodCondition is called with Ready type\n293: THEN nil should be returned\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ---\n297: \n298: ### REQ-003: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/finalizers.go\n299: \n300: **Description:** Implement unit tests for finalizer management functions.\n301: \n302: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n303: \n304: #### SCENARIO-034: AddFinalizer adds finalizer to object\n305: ```gherkin\n306: GIVEN a context\n307: AND a mock client.Client\n308: AND a client.Object without finalizers\n309: WHEN AddFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\n310: THEN the object should have \"test-finalizer\" in its finalizers list\n311: AND no error should be returned\n312: ```\n313: \n314: #### SCENARIO-035: AddFinalizer does not add duplicate finalizer\n315: ```gherkin\n316: GIVEN a context\n317: AND a mock client.Client\n318: AND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"existing\", \"test-finalizer\"]\n319: WHEN AddFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\n320: THEN the object should still have only two finalizers\n321: AND no error should be returned\n322: ```\n323: \n324: #### SCENARIO-036: AddFinalizer handles patch error\n325: ```gherkin\n326: GIVEN a context\n327: AND a mock client.Client that returns an error on Patch\n328: AND a client.Object without finalizers\n329: WHEN AddFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\n330: THEN an error should be returned\n331: AND the error message should contain \"failed to add finalizer\"\n332: ```\n333: \n334: #### SCENARIO-037: RemoveFinalizer removes finalizer from object\n335: ```gherkin\n336: GIVEN a context\n337: AND a mock client.Client\n338: AND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"keep-me\", \"remove-me\"]\n339: WHEN RemoveFinalizer is called with \"remove-me\"\n340: THEN the object should have only [\"keep-me\"] in its finalizers\n341: AND no error should be returned\n342: ```\n343: \n344: #### SCENARIO-038: RemoveFinalizer does nothing when finalizer not present\n345: ```gherkin\n346: GIVEN a context\n347: AND a mock client.Client\n348: AND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"keep-me\"]\n349: WHEN RemoveFinalizer is called with \"not-present\"\n350: THEN the object should still have [\"keep-me\"] in its finalizers\n351: AND no error should be returned\n352: ```\n353: \n354: #### SCENARIO-039: RemoveFinalizer handles patch error\n355: ```gherkin\n356: GIVEN a context\n357: AND a mock client.Client that returns an error on Patch\n358: AND a client.Object with finalizers = [\"test-finalizer\"]\n359: WHEN RemoveFinalizer is called with \"test-finalizer\"\n360: THEN an error should be returned\n361: AND the error message should contain \"failed to remove finalizer\"\n362: ```\n363: \n364: #### SCENARIO-040: HasFinalizer returns true when finalizer present\n365: ```gherkin\n366: GIVEN a client.Object with finalizers = [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]\n367: WHEN HasFinalizer is called with \"b\"\n368: THEN true should be returned\n369: ```\n370: \n371: #### SCENARIO-041: HasFinalizer returns false when finalizer absent\n372: ```gherkin\n373: GIVEN a client.Object with finalizers = [\"a\", \"c\"]\n374: WHEN HasFinalizer is called with \"b\"\n375: THEN false should be returned\n376: ```\n377: \n378: #### SCENARIO-042: GetOwnerReference returns UID when matching owner found\n379: ```gherkin\n380: GIVEN a metav1.Object with OwnerReferences\n381: AND one reference has APIVersion = \"v1\", Kind = \"Pod\", and UID = \"test-uid\"\n382: WHEN GetOwnerReference is called with APIVersion = \"v1\" and Kind = \"Pod\"\n383: THEN \"test-uid\" and true should be returned\n384: ```\n385: \n386: #### SCENARIO-043: GetOwnerReference returns empty when no matching owner\n387: ```gherkin\n388: GIVEN a metav1.Object with OwnerReferences\n389: AND none have the specified APIVersion and Kind\n390: WHEN GetOwnerReference is called with non-matching APIVersion and Kind\n391: THEN empty string and false should be returned\n392: ```\n393: \n394: ---\n395: \n396: ### REQ-004: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/status.go\n397: \n398: **Description:** Implement unit tests for status condition management functions.\n399: \n400: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n401: \n402: #### SCENARIO-044: SetCondition adds new condition to empty list\n403: ```gherkin\n404: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n405: AND a conditionType, status, reason, and message\n406: WHEN SetCondition is called\n407: THEN a new condition should be added to the list\n408: AND the condition should have the specified type, status, reason, and message\n409: AND LastTransitionTime should be set to current time\n410: ```\n411: \n412: #### SCENARIO-045: SetCondition updates existing condition with new status\n413: ```gherkin\n414: GIVEN a conditions list with a Ready condition with status = False\n415: AND new status = True\n416: WHEN SetCondition is called with Ready type and new status\n417: THEN the Ready condition should be updated to status = True\n418: AND LastTransitionTime should be updated to current time\n419: ```\n420: \n421: #### SCENARIO-046: SetCondition updates existing condition with same status\n422: ```gherkin\n423: GIVEN a conditions list with a Ready condition with status = True\n424: AND new status = True\n425: WHEN SetCondition is called with Ready type and same status\n426: THEN the Ready condition should retain status = True\n427: AND LastTransitionTime should be updated to current time\n428: AND reason and message should be updated\n429: ```\n430: \n431: #### SCENARIO-047: GetCondition returns matching condition\n432: ```gherkin\n433: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready, Available, and Progressing conditions\n434: WHEN GetCondition is called with Ready type\n435: THEN the Ready condition should be returned\n436: ```\n437: \n438: #### SCENARIO-048: GetCondition returns nil for missing condition type\n439: ```gherkin\n440: GIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\n441: WHEN GetCondition is called with Error type\n442: THEN nil should be returned\n443: ```\n444: \n445: #### SCENARIO-049: IsReady returns true when Ready condition is true\n446: ```gherkin\n447: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition status = ConditionTrue\n448: WHEN IsReady is called\n449: THEN true should be returned\n450: ```\n451: \n452: #### SCENARIO-050: IsReady returns false when Ready condition is false\n453: ```gherkin\n454: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition status = ConditionFalse\n455: WHEN IsReady is called\n456: THEN false should be returned\n457: ```\n458: \n459: #### SCENARIO-051: IsReady returns false when Ready condition missing\n460: ```gherkin\n461: GIVEN a conditions list without Ready condition\n462: WHEN IsReady is called\n463: THEN false should be returned\n464: ```\n465: \n466: #### SCENARIO-052: IsAvailable returns true when Available condition is true\n467: ```gherkin\n468: GIVEN a conditions list with Available condition status = ConditionTrue\n469: WHEN IsAvailable is called\n470: THEN true should be returned\n471: ```\n472: \n473: #### SCENARIO-053: IsProgressing returns true when Progressing condition is true\n474: ```gherkin\n475: GIVEN a conditions list with Progressing condition status = ConditionTrue\n476: WHEN IsProgressing is called\n477: THEN true should be returned\n478: ```\n479: \n480: #### SCENARIO-054: HasError returns true when Error condition is true\n481: ```gherkin\n482: GIVEN a conditions list with Error condition status = ConditionTrue\n483: WHEN HasError is called\n484: THEN true should be returned\n485: ```\n486: \n487: #### SCENARIO-055: SetReadyCondition sets Ready condition to true\n488: ```gherkin\n489: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n490: WHEN SetReadyCondition is called with ready = true\n491: THEN a Ready condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n492: ```\n493: \n494: #### SCENARIO-056: SetReadyCondition sets Ready condition to false\n495: ```gherkin\n496: GIVEN a conditions pointer with Ready condition\n497: WHEN SetReadyCondition is called with ready = false\n498: THEN the Ready condition should have status = ConditionFalse\n499: ```\n500: \n501: #### SCENARIO-057: SetErrorCondition sets Error condition with error message\n502: ```gherkin\n503: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n504: AND an error with message \"test error\"\n505: WHEN SetErrorCondition is called with the error\n506: THEN an Error condition should be added\n507: AND the message should contain \"test error\"\n508: ```\n509: \n510: #### SCENARIO-058: SetErrorCondition sets Error condition without error\n511: ```gherkin\n512: GIVEN a conditions pointer\n513: AND nil error\n514: WHEN SetErrorCondition is called with nil error\n515: THEN an Error condition with empty message should be set\n516: ```\n517: \n518: #### SCENARIO-059: ClearErrorCondition removes Error condition\n519: ```gherkin\n520: GIVEN a conditions list with Error condition\n521: WHEN ClearErrorCondition is called\n522: THEN the Error condition should be removed from the list\n523: ```\n524: \n525: #### SCENARIO-060: ClearErrorCondition does nothing when Error condition missing\n526: ```gherkin\n527: GIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\n528: WHEN ClearErrorCondition is called\n529: THEN the conditions list should remain unchanged\n530: ```\n531: \n532: #### SCENARIO-061: SetProgressingCondition sets Progressing condition\n533: ```gherkin\n534: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n535: WHEN SetProgressingCondition is called with progressing = true\n536: THEN a Progressing condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n537: ```\n538: \n539: #### SCENARIO-062: SetAvailableCondition sets Available condition\n540: ```gherkin\n541: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n542: WHEN SetAvailableCondition is called with available = true\n543: THEN an Available condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n544: ```\n545: \n546: #### SCENARIO-063: SetSandboxCreatedCondition sets SandboxCreated condition\n547: ```gherkin\n548: GIVEN a nil conditions pointer\n549: WHEN SetSandboxCreatedCondition is called with created = true\n550: THEN a SandboxCreated condition with status = ConditionTrue should be added\n551: ```\n552: \n553: #### SCENARIO-064: GetConditionMessage returns condition message\n554: ```gherkin\n555: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition message = \"ready message\"\n556: WHEN GetConditionMessage is called with Ready type\n557: THEN \"ready message\" should be returned\n558: ```\n559: \n560: #### SCENARIO-065: GetConditionMessage returns empty string for missing condition\n561: ```gherkin\n562: GIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\n563: WHEN GetConditionMessage is called with Error type\n564: THEN empty string should be returned\n565: ```\n566: \n567: #### SCENARIO-066: GetConditionReason returns condition reason\n568: ```gherkin\n569: GIVEN a conditions list with Ready condition reason = \"ReadyReason\"\n570: WHEN GetConditionReason is called with Ready type\n571: THEN \"ReadyReason\" should be returned\n572: ```\n573: \n574: #### SCENARIO-067: GetConditionReason returns empty string for missing condition\n575: ```gherkin\n576: GIVEN a conditions list without Error condition\n577: WHEN GetConditionReason is called with Error type\n578: THEN empty string should be returned\n579: ```\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ### REQ-005: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/errors.go\n584: \n585: **Description:** Implement unit tests for ReconcilerError types and constructors.\n586: \n587: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n588: \n589: #### SCENARIO-068: ReconcilerError.Error returns formatted message with wrapped error\n590: ```gherkin\n591: GIVEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"TestCode\", Message = \"Test message\", and Err = errors.New(\"wrapped\")\n592: WHEN Error is called\n593: THEN the result should contain \"TestCode: Test message (caused by: wrapped)\"\n594: ```\n595: \n596: #### SCENARIO-069: ReconcilerError.Error returns formatted message without wrapped error\n597: ```gherkin\n598: GIVEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"TestCode\", Message = \"Test message\", and Err = nil\n599: WHEN Error is called\n600: THEN the result should be \"TestCode: Test message\"\n601: ```\n602: \n603: #### SCENARIO-070: ReconcilerError.Unwrap returns wrapped error\n604: ```gherkin\n605: GIVEN a ReconcilerError with Err = errors.New(\"wrapped\")\n606: WHEN Unwrap is called\n607: THEN the wrapped error should be returned\n608: ```\n609: \n610: #### SCENARIO-071: ReconcilerError.Unwrap returns nil when no wrapped error\n611: ```gherkin\n612: GIVEN a ReconcilerError with Err = nil\n613: WHEN Unwrap is called\n614: THEN nil should be returned\n615: ```\n616: \n617: #### SCENARIO-072: NewReconcilerError creates error with all fields\n618: ```gherkin\n619: GIVEN code, message, err, and retryable parameters\n620: WHEN NewReconcilerError is called\n621: THEN a ReconcilerError with all fields set should be returned\n622: ```\n623: \n624: #### SCENARIO-073: NewValidationFailedError creates non-retryable error\n625: ```gherkin\n626: GIVEN message and err parameters\n627: WHEN NewValidationFailedError is called\n628: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"ValidationFailed\" and Retryable = false should be returned\n629: ```\n630: \n631: #### SCENARIO-074: NewSandboxCreateFailedError creates retryable error\n632: ```gherkin\n633: GIVEN message and err parameters\n634: WHEN NewSandboxCreateFailedError is called\n635: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"SandboxCreateFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n636: ```\n637: \n638: #### SCENARIO-075: NewSandboxUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n639: ```gherkin\n640: GIVEN message and err parameters\n641: WHEN NewSandboxUpdateFailedError is called\n642: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"SandboxUpdateFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n643: ```\n644: \n645: #### SCENARIO-076: NewSandboxDeleteFailedError creates retryable error\n646: ```gherkin\n647: GIVEN message and err parameters\n648: WHEN NewSandboxDeleteFailedError is called\n649: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"SandboxDeleteFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n650: ```\n651: \n652: #### SCENARIO-077: NewStatusUpdateFailedError creates retryable error\n653: ```gherkin\n654: GIVEN message and err parameters\n655: WHEN NewStatusUpdateFailedError is called\n656: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"StatusUpdateFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n657: ```\n658: \n659: #### SCENARIO-078: NewFinalizerFailedError creates retryable error\n660: ```gherkin\n661: GIVEN message and err parameters\n662: WHEN NewFinalizerFailedError is called\n663: THEN a ReconcilerError with Code = \"FinalizerFailed\" and Retryable = true should be returned\n664: ```\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ### REQ-006: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/controller.go\n669: \n670: **Description:** Implement unit tests for controller setup and configuration functions.\n671: \n672: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n673: \n674: #### SCENARIO-079: DefaultControllerConfig returns sensible defaults\n675: ```gherkin\n676: GIVEN no configuration provided\n677: WHEN DefaultControllerConfig is called\n678: THEN RequeueAfter should be 10 seconds\n679: AND MaxConcurrentReconciles should be 2\n680: AND EnableLeaderElection should be true\n681: AND LeaderElectionID should be \"agentcube-reconciler\"\n682: ```\n683: \n684: #### SCENARIO-080: NewControllerManager creates manager with config\n685: ```gherkin\n686: GIVEN a rest.Config\n687: AND a ControllerConfig with custom values\n688: WHEN NewControllerManager is called\n689: THEN a ctrl.Manager should be returned\n690: AND the manager should use the specified scheme\n691: AND no error should be returned\n692: ```\n693: \n694: #### SCENARIO-081: NewControllerManager handles error from ctrl.NewManager\n695: ```gherkin\n696: GIVEN an invalid rest.Config\n697: AND a ControllerConfig\n698: WHEN NewControllerManager is called\n699: THEN an error should be returned\n700: AND the error message should contain \"unable to start manager\"\n701: ```\n702: \n703: #### SCENARIO-082: GetSandboxName returns formatted name\n704: ```gherkin\n705: GIVEN a workload name \"test-workload\"\n706: WHEN GetSandboxName is called\n707: THEN \"test-workload-sandbox\" should be returned\n708: ```\n709: \n710: #### SCENARIO-083: GetSandboxName handles empty workload name\n711: ```gherkin\n712: GIVEN an empty workload name\n713: WHEN GetSandboxName is called\n714: THEN \"-sandbox\" should be returned\n715: ```\n716: \n717: ---\n718: \n719: ### REQ-007: Unit tests for controller/reconciler/metrics.go\n720: \n721: **Description:** Implement unit tests for Prometheus metrics recording functions.\n722: \n723: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n724: \n725: #### SCENARIO-084: RecordReconciliation increments reconcileTotal counter\n726: ```gherkin\n727: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n728: WHEN RecordReconciliation is called with controller, namespace, name, duration, and result\n729: THEN reconcileTotal counter should be incremented\n730: AND reconcileDuration histogram should observe the duration\n731: ```\n732: \n733: #### SCENARIO-085: RecordReconciliation increments reconcileRequeues on error result\n734: ```gherkin\n735: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n736: WHEN RecordReconciliation is called with result = \"error\"\n737: THEN reconcileRequeues counter should be incremented\n738: ```\n739: \n740: #### SCENARIO-086: RecordReconciliationError increments reconcileErrors counter\n741: ```gherkin\n742: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n743: WHEN RecordReconciliationError is called\n744: THEN reconcileErrors counter should be incremented\n745: ```\n746: \n747: #### SCENARIO-087: RecordRequeue increments reconcileRequeues counter\n748: ```gherkin\n749: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n750: WHEN RecordRequeue is called\n751: THEN reconcileRequeues counter should be incremented\n752: ```\n753: \n754: #### SCENARIO-088: RecordResourceReady increments resourcesReady gauge\n755: ```gherkin\n756: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n757: WHEN RecordResourceReady is called\n758: THEN resourcesReady gauge should be incremented\n759: ```\n760: \n761: #### SCENARIO-089: RecordResourcePending increments resourcesPending gauge\n762: ```gherkin\n763: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n764: WHEN RecordResourcePending is called\n765: THEN resourcesPending gauge should be incremented\n766: ```\n767: \n768: #### SCENARIO-090: RecordResourceError increments resourcesError gauge\n769: ```gherkin\n770: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n771: WHEN RecordResourceError is called\n772: THEN resourcesError gauge should be incremented\n773: ```\n774: \n775: #### SCENARIO-091: ClearResourceMetrics resets resource gauges to zero\n776: ```gherkin\n777: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics with non-zero values\n778: WHEN ClearResourceMetrics is called\n779: THEN resourcesReady gauge should be set to 0\n780: AND resourcesPending gauge should be set to 0\n781: AND resourcesError gauge should be set to 0\n782: ```\n783: \n784: #### SCENARIO-092: RecordSandboxCreation increments sandboxCreations counter\n785: ```gherkin\n786: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n787: WHEN RecordSandboxCreation is called\n788: THEN sandboxCreations counter should be incremented\n789: AND sandboxUpdateDuration histogram should observe the duration\n790: ```\n791: \n792: #### SCENARIO-093: RecordSandboxDeletion increments sandboxDeletions counter\n793: ```gherkin\n794: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n795: WHEN RecordSandboxDeletion is called\n796: THEN sandboxDeletions counter should be incremented\n797: AND sandboxUpdateDuration histogram should observe the duration\n798: ```\n799: \n800: #### SCENARIO-094: RecordSandboxUpdate records update duration\n801: ```gherkin\n802: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics\n803: WHEN RecordSandboxUpdate is called\n804: THEN sandboxUpdateDuration histogram should observe the duration with operation = \"update\"\n805: ```\n806: \n807: #### SCENARIO-095: ResetMetrics resets all metrics\n808: ```gherkin\n809: GIVEN initialized Prometheus metrics with non-zero values\n810: WHEN ResetMetrics is called\n811: THEN all metric counters should be reset\n812: AND all metric histograms should be reset\n813: AND all metric gauges should be reset\n814: ```\n815: \n816: ---\n817: \n818: ## Non-Requirements (Excluded from this task)\n819: \n820: The following files are excluded as they contain only constants, plain structs, or are better tested with integration tests:\n821: \n822: - `defaults.go` - Contains only constants\n823: - `api/types.go` - Contains only plain struct definitions\n824: - `types/sandbox_types.go` - Contains only plain struct definitions\n825: - `server/server.go` - Server lifecycle is better tested with integration/end-to-end tests\n826: - `controller/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go` - Complex reconciler logic is better tested with integration tests using envtest\n827: \n828: ---\n829: \n830: ## Test Coverage Goals\n831: \n832: Target coverage: **≥ 80%** for all tested files\n833: \n834: Priority order:\n835: 1. `auth/k8s_auth.go` - Critical security component\n836: 2. `controller/reconciler/predicates.go` - Core event filtering logic\n837: 3. `controller/reconciler/finalizers.go` - Resource cleanup safety\n838: 4. `controller/reconciler/status.go` - State management\n839: 5. `controller/reconciler/errors.go` - Error handling\n840: 6. `controller/reconciler/controller.go` - Controller setup\n841: 7. `controller/reconciler/metrics.go` - Observability\n842: \n843: ---\n844: \n845: ## Dependencies\n846: \n847: - `k8s.io/client-go` - Kubernetes client library (for mocks in auth tests)\n848: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` - Controller runtime (for mock client in reconciler tests)\n849: - `github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus` - Prometheus client (for metrics tests)\n850: - `github.com/stretchr/testify` - Testing assertions and mocks\n851: - `github.com/golang/mock` - Mock generation for k8s interfaces\n\n(End of file - total 851 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# delta-spec: AR-038 — Go 单元测试 (workloadmanager)\n\n## Overview\n\nModule: `pkg/workloadmanager`\nLanguage: Go\nSize: L\nTask: Add comprehensive unit tests for untested components\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Unit tests for auth/k8s_auth.go\n\n**Description:** Implement unit tests for K8sAuthenticator and TokenCache components.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n#### SCENARIO-001: K8sAuthenticator authenticates valid token\n```gherkin\nGIVEN a K8sAuthenticator configured with a kubernetes.Interface and audience","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775893226375,"end":1775893226389}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893226411,"sessionID":"ses_284842a70ffeQCCyWUKDRhFriu","part":{"id":"prt_d7b7c2368001z1gNOXwWPmwKNJ","messageID":"msg_d7b7c032d0012W5aPrQq672UfR","sessionID":"ses_284842a70ffeQCCyWUKDRhFriu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7c221333a1d44e26b676d8706f6da91d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 Delta Specification: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `AgentRuntime` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime type metadata and API group version\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `AgentRuntime`, and resource plural `agentruntimes`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n14: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n15: - **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n16: - **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `AgentRuntime`\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n19: - **GIVEN** a typed client for `AgentRuntime`\n20: - **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type\n21: - **THEN** resource name is `agentruntimes` in plural form\n22: \n23: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeSpec structure with required fields\n24: \n25: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct with required fields: `PodTemplate` of type `*SandboxTemplate`, `SessionTimeout` of type `*metav1.Duration`, and `MaxSessionDuration` of type `*metav1.Duration`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Spec requires pod template\n28: - **GIVEN** a new `AgentRuntime` object being created\n29: - **WHEN** the spec is populated\n30: - **THEN** `PodTemplate` must be non-nil and contains the sandbox pod template\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Duration fields use metav1 types\n33: - **GIVEN** an existing `AgentRuntime` with timeouts configured\n34: - **WHEN** the spec is serialized to YAML\n35: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` and `MaxSessionDuration` serialize as duration strings\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeStatus with conditions support\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct with optional `Conditions` field of type `[]metav1.Condition` for tracking runtime state transitions.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Status conditions are optional\n42: - **GIVEN** a newly created `AgentRuntime` resource\n43: - **WHEN** status is initially empty\n44: - **THEN** resource creation succeeds without requiring conditions\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Condition updates follow Kubernetes conventions\n47: - **GIVEN** a controller managing `AgentRuntime` lifecycle\n48: - **WHEN** transitioning between states (e.g., Creating → Running)\n49: - **THEN** conditions are added with appropriate types, reasons, and transition timestamps\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeList type for collection operations\n52: \n53: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeList` as a standard Kubernetes list type containing `[]AgentRuntime` items and standard list metadata.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: List type supports pagination\n56: - **GIVEN** multiple `AgentRuntime` resources in a namespace\n57: - **WHEN** `List` operation is called with `ListOptions.Limit`\n58: - **THEN** response returns an `AgentRuntimeList` with `Continue` token when more items exist\n59: \n60: ### Requirement: Scheme registration for serialization\n61: \n62: The system SHALL register `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in the Kubernetes scheme for proper JSON/YAML serialization and deserialization.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: YAML deserialization produces correct Go types\n65: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: AgentRuntime` in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group\n66: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded using the registered scheme\n67: - **THEN** an `AgentRuntime` struct instance is created with correct field mappings\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: List kind maps to AgentRuntimeList\n70: - **GIVEN** a YAML file containing `kind: AgentRuntimeList`\n71: - **WHEN** the YAML is decoded\n72: - **THEN** an `AgentRuntimeList` struct instance is created with items as `[]AgentRuntime`\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: CRD subresources support\n75: \n76: The system SHALL enable status subresource on `AgentRuntime` to allow independent updates to status without modifying spec.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Status update does not modify spec\n79: - **GIVEN** an existing `AgentRuntime` with both spec and status\n80: - **WHEN** a status-only update is performed via API server\n81: - **THEN** only status fields change and spec remains unmodified\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Status and spec have independent versioning\n84: - **GIVEN** a controller updating status\n85: - **WHEN** status changes multiple times\n86: - **THEN** each status update increments `metadata.generation` independently of spec modifications\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Default values for spec fields\n89: \n90: The system SHALL define kubebuilder markers to set default values: `SessionTimeout` defaults to `\"15m\"` and `MaxSessionDuration` defaults to `\"8h\"`.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Missing timeout fields receive defaults\n93: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` created without explicit timeout values\n94: - **WHEN** the resource is created via API\n95: - **THEN** `SessionTimeout` is set to `15m` and `MaxSessionDuration` to `8h` automatically\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Explicit values override defaults\n98: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` created with custom timeout values\n99: - **WHEN** the resource is created\n100: - **THEN** the explicit values are preserved and defaults are not applied\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: OpenAPI validation for spec fields\n103: \n104: The system SHALL generate OpenAPI v3 schema for `AgentRuntime` to enable validation of field types, required fields, and constraints.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Required field validation\n107: - **GIVEN** a request creating `AgentRuntime` without required `PodTemplate`\n108: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n109: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating `podTemplate` is required\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Type validation for duration fields\n112: - **GIVEN** a request creating `AgentRuntime` with invalid duration format\n113: - **WHEN** the API server validates the request\n114: - **THEN** validation fails with error about invalid duration format\n115: \n116: ### Requirement: Print columns for kubectl readability\n117: \n118: The system SHALL configure additional printer columns for `kubectl get` output, including `Age` derived from `metadata.creationTimestamp`.\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Age column displays correctly\n121: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` resource that was created 5 minutes ago\n122: - **WHEN** `kubectl get agentruntimes` is executed\n123: - **THEN** the Age column shows `5m` or equivalent time duration\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: CRD status storage optimization\n126: \n127: The system SHALL use status subresource to ensure status updates are stored efficiently and do not trigger spec reconciliation unnecessarily.\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Frequent status updates\n130: - **GIVEN** a controller updating `AgentRuntime` status every 30 seconds\n131: - **WHEN** multiple status updates occur\n132: - **THEN** each update only writes to status subresource and does not trigger full reconciliation\n133: \n134: ### Requirement: Type registration in code-generation\n135: \n136: The system SHALL ensure `AgentRuntime` types are included in the client-go code-generation pipeline to produce typed clients, informers, and listers.\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Typed client operations work\n139: - **GIVEN** a `Clientset` instance from generated client-go code\n140: - **WHEN** calling `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create`\n141: - **THEN** the operation succeeds with proper type safety and returns an `AgentRuntime` pointer\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Informer factory recognizes AgentRuntime\n144: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` for the runtime API group\n145: - **WHEN** `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` is called\n146: - **THEN** an informer watching `agentruntimes` resources is returned\n147: \n148: ### Requirement: JSON tag naming convention\n149: \n150: The system SHALL use camelCase JSON tags for all fields to match Kubernetes API conventions and client-go expectations.\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: JSON serialization uses camelCase\n153: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` struct populated with Go fields\n154: - **WHEN** serialized to JSON\n155: - **THEN** the JSON keys are camelCase (e.g., `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `maxSessionDuration`)\n156: \n157: ### Requirement: DeepCopy methods for safety\n158: \n159: The system SHALL implement `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopyObject` methods for `AgentRuntime` to support safe copying in controllers.\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: DeepCopy creates independent instance\n162: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` instance with populated fields\n163: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy` is called\n164: - **THEN** the returned copy is independent and modifications to the copy do not affect the original\n165: \n166: ### Requirement: Validation markers for fields\n167: \n168: The system SHALL use kubebuilder validation markers to enforce constraints on spec fields where applicable.\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Duration fields validate format\n171: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` with `SessionTimeout` set to invalid duration\n172: - **WHEN** the resource is submitted to the API server\n173: - **THEN** validation fails with error indicating invalid duration format\n174: \n175: ### Requirement: Label selector support for listing\n176: \n177: The system SHALL support standard Kubernetes label selectors when listing `AgentRuntime` resources.\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Label selector filters results\n180: - **GIVEN** multiple `AgentRuntime` resources with different labels\n181: - **WHEN** `List` is called with a label selector matching a specific label\n182: - **THEN** only resources matching the selector are returned\n183: \n184: ### Requirement: Watch support for controller integration\n185: \n186: The system SHALL support watch operations on `AgentRuntime` resources to enable controllers to react to changes efficiently.\n187: \n188: #### Scenario: Watch events notify of changes\n189: - **GIVEN** a watch stream established on `AgentRuntime` resources\n190: - **WHEN** a new `AgentRuntime` is created\n191: - **THEN** the watch stream receives an ADDED event with the new resource\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 Delta Specification: CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine Go type definitions and Kubernetes CRD registration for the `AgentRuntime` custom resource in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group, including integration with the generated client-go library and proper API machinery support.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime type metadata and API group version\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes custom resource with `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group, `v1alpha1` version, kind `AgentRuntime`, and resource plural `agentruntimes`.\n\n#### Scenario: Type metadata reflects GVR mapping\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API server resolving the CRD type\n- **WHEN** the `TypeMeta` fields are inspected\n- **THEN** `APIVersion` is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and `Kind` is `AgentRuntime`\n\n#### Scenario: Resource plural matches client-go expectations\n- **GIVEN** a typed client for `AgentRuntime`\n- **WHEN** constructing a `GroupVersionResource` from the type","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-001/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775893226379,"end":1775893226408}}}}
